The Minister of Science and Technology,Â  Dr Ogbonnaya Onu has tasked Nigerian professionals to brace the new Executive Order 5. The minister said professionals should bid for contracts with foreign firms in all sectors of the economy, particularly in the areas of expertise that require more technical prowess. Dr Onu made the call when he presided over a world press briefing on the Presidential Executive Order 5 yesterday in Lagos, a statement from the ministry said. The current Executive Order gives preference to Nigerian firms in the award of contracts and employing consultants regardless of experience and timeline of operations, especially as regards national security, indigenous firms would be entrusted and preferred. He read out the major sections of the Executive Order, which is made up of 18 sections stretching from preferences, accreditation, tax incentives to definition of terms and effective date of the Order